15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-400 of Title 2, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no person, firm,
20 association, corporation, or any other entity of this state shall
21 manufacture, compound, brew, distill, produce, process, sell,
22 deliver, distribute, hold, offer, or expose for sale any of the
23 following substances as food additives or food color additives or
24 any other food product beginning on January 15, 2027, or those
Req. No. 1884 Page 1

1 addi tives or color additives used to reformulate ingestible drugs
2 beginning on January 18, 2028, that contain any of the following
3 substances:
4 1. Blue dye 1;
5 2. Blue dye 2;
6 3. Green dye 3;
7 4. Red dye 3;
8 5. Red dye 40;
9 6. Yellow dye 5; or
10 7. Yellow dye 6.
11 B. Upon the issuance of a revocation of authorization for use
12 by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration, the prohibition as set
13 forth in subsection A of this section shall extend to the following
14 additives:
15 1. Aspartame;
16 2. Azodicarbonamide (ADA);
17 3. Brominated vegetable oil (BVO);
18 4 Butylated hydroxyanisole (BHA);
19 5. Butylated hydroxytoluene (BHT);
20 6. Ethylene dichloride;
21 7. Methylene chloride;
22 8. Potassium bromate;
23 9. Propyl gallate;
24 10. Propylparaben;
